verses.text_plain: Truly God is good to Israel, even to such as are of a clean heart.
verses.verse_html:
1Truly God is good to Israel, even to such as are of a clean heart. ▼
▼ of: or, for
 , ▼
▼ Truly: or, Yet
 , ▼
▼ of…: Heb. clean of heart

tokens.text: to such as are of a clean

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: Heb. clean of heart

verses.text_plain: But as for me, my feet were almost gone; my steps had well nigh slipped.
verses.verse_html: 2But as for me, my feet were almost gone; my steps had well nigh slipped.

tokens.text: But as for me, my feet

verses.text_plain: For I was envious at the foolish, when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
verses.verse_html: 3For I was envious at the foolish, when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.

verses.text_plain: For there are no bands in their death: but their strength is firm.
verses.verse_html:
4For there are no bands in their death: but their strength is firm. ▼
▼ firm: Heb. fat

verses.text_plain: They are not in trouble as other men; neither are they plagued like other men.
verses.verse_html:
5They are not in trouble as other men; neither are they plagued like other men. ▼
▼ in…: Heb. in the trouble of other men
 , ▼
▼ like: Heb. with

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in…: Heb. in the trouble of other men
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: Heb. in the trouble of other men

verses.text_plain: Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain; violence covereth them as a garment.
verses.verse_html: 6Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain; violence covereth them as a garment.

tokens.text: compasseth them about as a chain

verses.text_plain: Their eyes stand out with fatness: they have more than heart could wish.
verses.verse_html:
7Their eyes stand out with fatness: they have more than heart could wish. ▼
▼ have…: Heb. pass the thoughts of the heart

footnotes.body_text: ▼ have…: Heb. pass the thoughts of the heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ have…: Heb. pass the thoughts of the heart

verses.text_plain: They are corrupt, and speak wickedly concerning oppression: they speak loftily.
verses.verse_html: 8They are corrupt, and speak wickedly concerning oppression: they speak loftily.

verses.text_plain: They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walketh through the earth.
verses.verse_html: 9They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walketh through the earth.

verses.text_plain: Therefore his people return hither: and waters of a full cup are wrung out to them.
verses.verse_html: 10Therefore his people return hither: and waters of a full cup are wrung out to them.

verses.text_plain: And they say, How doth God know? and is there knowledge in the most High?
verses.verse_html: 11And they say, How doth God know? and is there knowledge in the most High?

verses.text_plain: Behold, these are the ungodly, who prosper in the world; they increase in riches.
verses.verse_html: 12Behold, these are the ungodly, who prosper in the world; they increase in riches.

verses.text_plain: Verily I have cleansed my heart in vain, and washed my hands in innocency.
verses.verse_html: 13Verily I have cleansed my heart in vain, and washed my hands in innocency.

verses.text_plain: For all the day long have I been plagued, and chastened every morning.
verses.verse_html:
14For all the day long have I been plagued, and chastened every morning. ▼
▼ chastened: Heb. my chastisement was

footnotes.body_html: ▼ chastened: Heb. my chastisement was

verses.text_plain: If I say, I will speak thus; behold, I should offend against the generation of thy children.
verses.verse_html: 15If I say, I will speak thus; behold, I should offend against the generation of thy children.

verses.text_plain: When I thought to know this, it was too painful for me;
verses.verse_html:
16When I thought to know this, it was too painful for me; ▼
▼ too…: Heb. labour in mine eyes

footnotes.body_text: ▼ too…: Heb. labour in mine eyes
footnotes.body_html: ▼ too…: Heb. labour in mine eyes

verses.text_plain: Until I went into the sanctuary of God; then understood I their end.
verses.verse_html: 17Until I went into the sanctuary of God; then understood I their end.

verses.text_plain: Surely thou didst set them in slippery places: thou castedst them down into destruction.
verses.verse_html: 18Surely thou didst set them in slippery places: thou castedst them down into destruction.

verses.text_plain: How are they brought into desolation, as in a moment! they are utterly consumed with terrors.
verses.verse_html: 19How are they brought into desolation, as in a moment! they are utterly consumed with terrors.

verses.text_plain: As a dream when one awaketh; so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.
verses.verse_html: 20As a dream when one awaketh; so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.

verses.text_plain: Thus my heart was grieved, and I was pricked in my reins.
verses.verse_html: 21Thus my heart was grieved, and I was pricked in my reins.

verses.text_plain: So foolish was I, and ignorant: I was as a beast before thee.
verses.verse_html:
22So foolish was I, and ignorant: I was as a beast before thee. ▼
▼ ignorant: Heb. I knew not
 , ▼
▼ before: Heb. with

footnotes.body_html: ▼ ignorant: Heb. I knew not

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless I am continually with thee: thou hast holden me by my right hand.
verses.verse_html: 23Nevertheless I am continually with thee: thou hast holden me by my right hand.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel, and afterward receive me to glory.
verses.verse_html: 24Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel, and afterward receive me to glory.

verses.text_plain: Whom have I in heaven but thee? and there is none upon earth that I desire beside thee.
verses.verse_html: 25Whom have I in heaven but thee? and there is none upon earth that I desire beside thee.

verses.text_plain: My flesh and my heart faileth: but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever.
verses.verse_html:
26My flesh and my heart faileth: but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever. ▼
▼ strength: Heb. rock

verses.text_plain: For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee.
verses.verse_html: 27For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee.

tokens.text: For, lo, they that are far
all them that go a whoring

verses.text_plain: But it is good for me to draw near to God: I have put my trust in the Lord God, that I may declare all thy works.
verses.verse_html: 28But it is good for me to draw near to God: I have put my trust in the Lord God, that I may declare all thy works.
